            "answer": "The correct answer is A. FP16 commonly halves memory footprint and improves tensor-core utilization without the calibration burden or notable accuracy loss seen in more aggressive quantization. INT8 can be faster still, so the claim that FP16 always beats it is too strong and misses the actual trade-off structure.",
            "learning_objective": "Evaluate serving precision options in terms of latency, memory, and accuracy."
