              "JIT can specialize to observed runtime shapes but may make early requests pay a compilation penalty, while AOT shifts that work before deployment.",
              "JIT improves portability, while AOT guarantees dynamic retraining during serving.",
              "There is no practical difference once the model is exported."
            ],
            "answer": "The correct answer is B. JIT can optimize based on real execution patterns but often pushes cost into the first live requests; AOT front-loads compilation to avoid that startup spike. The alternatives either invent properties like dynamic retraining or ignore the real cold-start implications discussed in the section.",
            "learning_objective": "Compare JIT and AOT compilation in terms of serving latency and deployment behavior."
