            "question_type": "SHORT",
            "question": "Why can CPU-only inference require thread pinning and NUMA awareness even when the model itself is already well optimized?",
            "answer": "On multi-socket systems, remote memory access and thread migration can add substantial latency and jitter that have nothing to do with the model's arithmetic efficiency. Pinning threads and co-locating memory keep data local to the serving cores, which improves both latency and consistency.",
