            "answer": "The correct answer is C. Safetensors is fast because the format is simple and mmap-friendly, so loading approaches the storage device's raw read performance rather than Python parsing overhead. Automatic quantization or network-to-GPU bypass is not the mechanism described in the chapter.",
            "learning_objective": "Explain how serialization format influences cold-start performance."
